            <bug_when>2011-04-11 11:37:41 -0700</bug_when>
            <thetext>This was something we considered when implementing HSTS, but the security gain from its use outweighs the privacy encroachment (especially since sites can simply use cookies or your disk/image cache).

We implemented proper private browsing mode support (bug 557598: HSTS data accumulated in private mode will be erased when exiting private mode) to mitigate local-adversary concerns. 

Perhaps it would be worth exploring the addition of an about:config pref to disable HSTS for the ten people who want to disable this feature?</thetext>
